    "comment": "Rationale: Fig 9A: Snx6 gene was eliminated in a small subset of hippocampal neurons by injection of organotypic hippocampal slice culture from Snx6fl/fl mouse with recombinant adeno-associated virus (AAV) coexpressing EGFP and the Cre recombinase.\nFig 9B-D: Results from simultaneous recording the evoked EPSCs (eEPSCs) on infected and adjacent uninfected CA1 pyramidal neurons showed that AMPAR-mediated eEPSCs were significantly impaired by about 50% with ablation of SNX6 whereas NMDAR-mediated eEPSCs and the pair-pulse ratio of AMPAR eEPSCs was unaffected indicating that the impairment of AMPAR eEPSCs is due to decrease in the number of AMPARs in the postsynaptic membrane but not the reduction of presynaptic glutamate release.\nFig 9G-J: A decrease in the surface expression of GluA1 and GluA2 was observed in Nestin Cre SNX6 fl/fl (KO) neurons as compared to SNX6 fl/fl (control). This effect was fully rescued by overexpressing SNX6.. Experimental description: SNX6 CNS-specific knockouts were generated by crossing Snx6fl/fl mice with Nestin-Cre mice.",
